MTV NETWORKS

00:40.123 --> 00:42.041
[♪...]

00:46.212 --> 00:49.799
{\an3}WHOA.

00:49.883 --> 00:53.303
LOOK AT THOSE AWESOME PROPS.

00:53.386 --> 00:55.305
THE MULTIPLE BACKDROPS.

00:55.388 --> 00:58.099
THAT ATTENTION TO DETAIL.

00:58.183 --> 01:00.810
{\an5}IT'S LIKE GOING ON
A MAGICAL JOURNEY THROUGH
THE WORLD OF PICTURES.

01:00.894 --> 01:03.980
Portia: THOSE
ARE FRITZ ORIGINALS.

01:04.063 --> 01:05.355
{\an3}HERE.

01:05.440 --> 01:08.359
{\an3}TWO YEARS WORTH OF TAFFY
ORDER FORMS, PER YOUR REQUEST.

01:08.443 --> 01:09.152
{\an3}BYE.

01:09.235 --> 01:09.611
WAIT.

01:09.694 --> 01:12.572
WHO'S FRITZ?

01:12.655 --> 01:14.365
IS FRITZ THE PHOTOGRAPHER?

01:14.449 --> 01:16.493
HOW DID YOU MEET THIS FRITZ?

01:16.576 --> 01:17.327
[LAUGHING]

01:17.410 --> 01:17.952
YOU'RE A DORK.

01:18.036 --> 01:19.871
FRITZ IS IN THE MALL.

01:19.954 --> 01:21.748
EVERYBODY KNOWS THAT.

01:21.831 --> 01:23.500
OH, SO HE'S FAMOUS.

01:23.583 --> 01:25.126
OF COURSE.

01:25.210 --> 01:28.421
PORTIA, THESE PORTRAITS
ARE ABSOLUTELY GLAMOROUS.

01:28.505 --> 01:30.131
{\an3}YEAH, WELL,
WE'RE REALLY PHOTOGENIC.

01:34.677 --> 01:36.679
HAPS, ARE YOU THINKING
WHAT I'M THINKING?

01:36.763 --> 01:38.348
{\an3}[GRUMBLING]

01:38.431 --> 01:39.599
{\an1}EXACTLY.

01:39.682 --> 01:41.851
{\an1}WE SHOULD HAVE FRITZ
TAKE OUR PORTRAIT.

01:41.935 --> 01:44.187
YEAH, YOU SHOULD LEAVE HERE NOW
AND GO DO THAT.

01:44.270 --> 01:46.064
[GROANING]

01:46.147 --> 01:47.899
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT EITHER.

01:47.982 --> 01:51.194
{\an3}WE FINALLY FOUND SOMEONE
WHO HAS THE VISUAL GRAMMAR

01:51.277 --> 01:54.447
{\an3}TO EXPRESS THE LAYERED BEAUTY
OF OUR RELATIONSHIP.

01:54.531 --> 01:55.198
THIRD FLOOR.

01:55.281 --> 01:57.575
TAKE A RIGHT AT CASUAL FRIDAY'S.

01:57.659 --> 01:59.994
ACROSS FROM ROJO'S HOT PRETZELS.

02:00.078 --> 02:02.205
NEXT TO THE EARRING TREE.

02:02.288 --> 02:04.666
UNDERNEATH THE BANGLE BARN.

02:04.749 --> 02:06.459
[GRUMBLING]

02:06.543 --> 02:08.086
I KNOW, BOY.

02:08.169 --> 02:10.213
I'M EXCITED TOO.

02:10.295 --> 02:12.632
[GASPING]

02:12.715 --> 02:14.634
[GROWLING]

02:21.349 --> 02:22.559
{\an1}[GRUNTING]

02:22.642 --> 02:24.394
{\an3}[LAUGHING]

02:24.477 --> 02:27.564
[ALL MAKING NOISES AT ONCE]

02:27.647 --> 02:31.359
FRAU GARCIA, I CAN SEE YOUR
FLIP-FLOPS UNDER YOUR PETTICOAT.

02:32.861 --> 02:36.531
PLEASE.

02:36.614 --> 02:38.449
HOW DID I GET HERE?

02:38.533 --> 02:39.409
THIS ISN'T ART.

02:39.492 --> 02:41.703
OH.

02:41.786 --> 02:45.123
{\an1}[GROWLING]

02:45.206 --> 02:47.876
OH, HAPPY, CAN'T IT WAIT?

02:47.959 --> 02:48.668
[WHINING]

02:48.751 --> 02:50.920
OK, USE THE CAN.

02:51.004 --> 02:53.590
BUT MAKE IT QUICK.

02:53.673 --> 02:55.592
SO GLAMOROUS!

02:55.675 --> 02:56.801
WHO ARE YOU?

02:56.885 --> 02:58.469
{\an1}AND WHERE IS
YOUR LEGAL GUARDIAN?

02:58.553 --> 03:01.431
[GASPING]

03:01.514 --> 03:04.601
[SQUEAKING]

03:05.643 --> 03:10.523
I... BESSIE... YOU... YOU'RE...

03:10.607 --> 03:15.528
YOUR USE OF BACKDROPS AND PROPS
IS JUST... MASTERPIECES.

03:17.322 --> 03:19.198
WHAT WOULD IT TAKE
FOR YOU TO CONSIDER...

03:22.452 --> 03:25.455
{\an1}$19.95.

03:31.502 --> 03:34.339
UM, FRITZ?

03:34.422 --> 03:36.549
UM, WHAT IS YOUR FEELING
ABOUT GLITTER BORDERS?

03:36.633 --> 03:38.176
FINE.

03:38.259 --> 03:39.302
ME TOO.

03:39.385 --> 03:41.054
I JUST LOVE THINGS
THAT SHIMMER, SO...

03:44.057 --> 03:45.141
OH, WAIT!

03:45.224 --> 03:47.018
CHEESE!

03:47.101 --> 03:49.896
[TOILET FLUSHING]

03:49.979 --> 03:52.941
CHEESE!

03:53.024 --> 03:54.150
{\an3}[GAGGING]

03:54.233 --> 03:55.985
[GASPING]

03:56.069 --> 03:57.236
A DOG?

03:57.320 --> 04:01.532
A SLOBBERING, DROOLING,
STINKING DOG?

04:01.616 --> 04:04.452
THIS IS WHAT
I'VE BEEN REDUCED TO?

04:04.535 --> 04:06.371
I CAN'T TAKE IT ANYMORE!

04:09.415 --> 04:10.500
BUT, FRITZ.

04:10.583 --> 04:12.168
BUT NOTHING.

04:12.251 --> 04:16.839
{\an5}I DO NOT WORK
WITH PRIMITIVE LIFE FORMS
UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCE.

04:16.923 --> 04:20.093
I HAVE LOOKED INTO THE ABYSS,
AND THE ABYSS HAS LOOKED BACK

04:20.176 --> 04:22.804
AND DO YOU KNOW
WHAT IT HAS SAID?

04:25.264 --> 04:29.060
LOSER.

04:29.143 --> 04:31.437
{\an1}I QUIT!

04:31.521 --> 04:33.773
{\an3}[SOBBING]

04:33.856 --> 04:36.275
[LAUGHING]

04:41.614 --> 04:43.992
LOOK, HAPS, YOU CAN'T
TAKE IT PERSONALLY.

04:44.075 --> 04:47.203
AND YOU CERTAINLY CAN'T
LET IT GET YOU DOWN.

04:47.286 --> 04:49.080
I MEAN, YOU'RE A SOPHISTICATED,
THOUGHTFUL, WORLDLY GUY

04:49.163 --> 04:52.834
WHO JUST HAPPENS TO BE
COVERED WITH FUR.

04:52.917 --> 04:54.419
FRITZ JUST DOESN'T GET IT YET.

04:54.502 --> 04:57.964
BUT DON'T WORRY, HAPS,
'CAUSE I AM GOING TO ENSURE

04:58.047 --> 05:03.052
{\an5}THAT OUR UNIQUE BOND IS CAPTURED
IN A GLOSSY 8x10,
AND SOME 4x6 WALLET-SIZES TOO.

05:03.136 --> 05:04.554
[GRUMBLING]

05:16.691 --> 05:20.737
[SIGHING]

05:20.820 --> 05:24.449
MY LIFE.

05:24.532 --> 05:27.910
OK, HAPS.

05:27.994 --> 05:29.620
LET'S SHOW 'EM
WHAT YOU'RE MADE OF.

05:29.704 --> 05:30.079
[CLEARING THROAT]

05:30.163 --> 05:32.081
HAPPY, LOOK!

05:32.165 --> 05:34.959
THAT CAN OF BABY BACK RIBS
IS IN DANGER.

05:35.043 --> 05:37.670
IF ONLY THERE WERE
A HERO TO SAVE IT.

05:56.773 --> 05:59.233
[SHRIEKING]

05:59.317 --> 06:01.986
WHOO-HOO!

06:02.070 --> 06:03.279
A 10!

06:03.362 --> 06:06.032
WOW, ISN'T HE THE MOST GRACEFUL
CREATURE YOU'VE EVER SEEN?

06:06.115 --> 06:11.120
[GAGGING...]

06:12.288 --> 06:13.247
{\an1}PHOOEY.

06:13.331 --> 06:15.875
SO HOW ABOUT THAT PHOTO?

06:15.958 --> 06:20.588
{\an4}12 YEARS OF ART SCHOOL
SO I CAN PHOTOGRAPH
SLOPPY FAMILIES IN CLOWN SUITS?

06:21.380 --> 06:23.800
{\an1}UGH.

06:23.883 --> 06:26.135
NOBODY UNDERSTANDS...

06:26.219 --> 06:28.805
...WHAT IT IS LIKE IN HERE.

06:32.892 --> 06:35.228
MAYBE I SHOULD HAVE BEEN
A TRAVEL AGENT.

06:35.311 --> 06:37.146
MAYBE I JUST NEED TO BE HELD.

06:37.230 --> 06:40.149
[WHIMPERING]

06:40.233 --> 06:40.983
{\an3}HUGS?

06:41.067 --> 06:43.069
HOW UN-DOG-LIKE.

06:43.152 --> 06:47.323
{\an3}BOY, YOU KNOW HAPPY
IS SO SENSITIVE, SO HUMAN.

06:47.406 --> 06:49.408
{\an3}WHY NOT CAPTURE THAT SENSITIVITY
IN A NICE PHOTO?

06:53.329 --> 06:57.166
{\an3}HM, AN AFTERNOON AT THE CINEMA
WAS A BRILLIANT IDEA, HAPPY.

06:57.250 --> 06:58.334
THANK YOU FOR SUGGESTING IT.

06:58.417 --> 06:59.877
YOU HAVE A LOT OF CLASS,
I TELL YOU.

06:59.961 --> 07:01.629
A LOT OF CLASS.

07:04.966 --> 07:07.802
[THUNDER]

07:07.885 --> 07:09.512
[SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

07:09.595 --> 07:14.142
BLECH, BLECH, BLECH,
THAT'S A POODLE SKIRT.

07:14.225 --> 07:18.354
{\an5}[LAUGHING]

07:14.225 --> 07:18.354
{\an1}[GROWLING]

07:18.437 --> 07:22.066
[MAN IN FILM SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

07:22.150 --> 07:23.860
BLECH, BLECH, BLECH, BLECH,
BLECH, BLECH, BLECH, BLECH.

07:23.943 --> 07:27.738
[LAUGHING]

07:27.822 --> 07:30.158
DO YOU MIND?

07:30.241 --> 07:31.534
MIND?

07:31.617 --> 07:34.203
HAPPY JUST LOVES
FOREIGN PICTURES.

07:34.287 --> 07:35.746
HE'S VERY CONTINENTAL.

07:40.126 --> 07:42.378
{\an1}SPEAKING OF PICTURES,
HOW ABOUT ONE OF ME AND MY DOG?

07:45.464 --> 07:47.133
[GENERAL CONVERSATION...]

07:47.216 --> 07:49.635
NOW THIS IS ART.

07:49.719 --> 07:53.264
BACK TO MY ROOTS.

07:53.347 --> 07:56.309
Bessie: LADIES AND LIZARDS,
GATHER AROUND.

07:57.185 --> 07:59.604
DO YOU WANT TO SEE
A DOG BOY JUGGLE?

07:59.687 --> 08:03.774
{\an3}I SAID, DO YOU WANT TO SEE
A DOG BOY JUGGLE?

08:03.858 --> 08:06.360
WHO WANTS TO SEE
A DOG BOY JUGGLE?

08:06.444 --> 08:09.238
NICE CATCH, HAPS.

08:09.322 --> 08:10.156
AND JUGGLE.

08:10.239 --> 08:12.200
[HAPPY WHIMPERING]

08:12.283 --> 08:15.620
NOW, LET'S TURN UP THE HEAT.

08:15.703 --> 08:16.579
[HAPPY WHIMPERING]

08:20.499 --> 08:21.167
{\an3}Bessie: OH!

08:21.250 --> 08:21.626
{\an3}OH, FRITZ.

08:21.709 --> 08:22.210
I'M SO SORRY.

08:22.293 --> 08:23.961
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

08:24.045 --> 08:27.965
{\an5}I WAS JUST TRYING TO SHOW YOU
WHAT A GREAT PHOTO MODEL
HAPPY COULD BE.

08:28.049 --> 08:30.218
[GASPING]

08:30.301 --> 08:32.094
PHOTO?

08:32.178 --> 08:35.181
{\an5}I WILL NEVER SHOOT A PHOTO
OF YOU AND YOUR FILTHY POOCH
AS LONG AS I LIVE.

08:35.264 --> 08:38.433
SURE I CAN'T CHANGE YOUR MIND?

08:38.517 --> 08:39.936
<i>NEIN!</i>

08:45.858 --> 08:51.572
[SOBBING...]

09:19.892 --> 09:23.604
[CAMERA SNAPPING...]

09:23.688 --> 09:25.231
Fritz: DUCHAMP.

09:25.314 --> 09:27.567
WARHOL.

09:27.650 --> 09:29.360
MAN RAY.

09:29.443 --> 09:30.486
[DOOR OPENING AND BELL RINGING]

09:30.569 --> 09:33.364
WHO'S THERE?

09:33.447 --> 09:36.367
WHOEVER YOU ARE,
I HAVE YOU ON FILM.

09:36.450 --> 09:37.285
I'LL GET YOU!

09:44.583 --> 09:46.377
[BESSIE SOBBING...]

09:46.460 --> 09:48.796
[DOORBELL RINGING]

10:00.099 --> 10:03.352
I AM HERE ABOUT YOUR DOG, HAPPY.

10:03.436 --> 10:06.314
HE IS A TRUE...

10:09.108 --> 10:09.900
INSPIRATION.

10:09.984 --> 10:12.194
AND I WAS WAY
TOO BLIND TO SEE IT.

10:12.278 --> 10:15.740
OH, WHAT A RUT I WAS IN.

10:15.823 --> 10:16.532
PLEASE, FORGIVE ME.

10:16.615 --> 10:19.618
YOU WERE RIGHT AND I WAS WRONG.

10:19.702 --> 10:24.665
[SOBBING...]

10:30.880 --> 10:34.216
HAPPY... HAPPY IS THE MUSE
I HAVE LONGED FOR.

10:35.426 --> 10:40.639
THE PHOTOS I TOOK OF HIM ARE,
QUITE FRANKLY, BRILLIANT.

10:40.723 --> 10:44.560
AND NOW, I NEED YOU
TO SIGN THIS FORM.

10:44.644 --> 10:45.561
{\an3}FOR WHAT?

10:45.644 --> 10:48.064
{\an1}SO I CAN SELL
YOUR DOG'S PICTURES.

10:48.147 --> 10:50.983
I'VE GOT BUYERS LINED ALL
THE WAY UP THE ESCALATOR.

10:52.151 --> 10:53.819
{\an3}WHATEVER.

11:05.873 --> 11:07.500
{\an3}THEY'RE DELIGHTFUL AND SCARY
AT THE SAME TIME.

11:07.583 --> 11:09.377
{\an1}I DON'T GET THEM,
BUT I GET THEM.

11:09.460 --> 11:10.586
DO YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

11:10.669 --> 11:14.256
{\an3}IT MAKES ME WANT
TO RETHINK MY WHOLE LIFE.

11:14.340 --> 11:16.092
I'LL BE HONEST.

11:16.175 --> 11:17.218
I LIKE YOUR EARLIER WORK.

11:17.301 --> 11:20.471
{\an3}BUT IF THIS IS WHAT FLOATS
YOUR BOAT, I'LL SIGN.

11:20.554 --> 11:21.514
[HIGH-PITCHED LAUGHTER]

11:21.597 --> 11:22.932
ON ONE CONDITION.

11:23.015 --> 11:24.350
[CAMERA SNAPPING]

11:26.018 --> 11:32.733
[♪...]

11:43.994 --> 11:46.622
SAVE-THE-DATES FOR NEXT YEAR'S
BIRTHDAY, DONE.

11:46.705 --> 11:48.541
SHOELACES IN FALL
COLORS, ORDERED.

11:48.624 --> 11:50.793
HIVE GAS BILL, PREPAID.

11:50.876 --> 11:53.129
FOR YOU, BESSIE.

11:53.212 --> 11:55.423
A BONUS GIFT FROM HONEYBEE H.Q.

11:55.506 --> 11:58.717
YOU WERE THE TOP REGIONAL
TAFFY SELLER LAST SEASON.

11:58.801 --> 12:00.136
COME AND GET IT.

12:00.219 --> 12:02.012
OH, BOY!

12:02.096 --> 12:05.433
OH.

12:05.516 --> 12:06.475
IT'S, UM...

12:06.559 --> 12:09.478
UH, UH-HUH.

12:09.562 --> 12:13.858
WELL, IT'S A LITTLE
ABSTRACT FOR ME.

12:14.442 --> 12:16.735
BUT ANYWAY, WHO CARES?

12:16.819 --> 12:18.696
IT'S ABOUT RECOGNIZING
MY HIGH LEVEL OF ACHIEVEMENTS.

12:18.779 --> 12:21.365
[GASPING]

12:21.449 --> 12:24.702
A MAGICAL EYEBALL POSTER.

12:24.785 --> 12:25.619
OK, STAND BACK.

12:25.703 --> 12:26.745
I'M TOTALLY GOOD AT THIS.

12:30.875 --> 12:32.084
LOOK AT THE PICTURE, YOU GUYS.

12:32.168 --> 12:34.920
ISN'T IT CRAZY?

12:35.004 --> 12:37.548
{\an3}I SEE IT.

12:37.631 --> 12:38.799
WELL, OK.

12:38.883 --> 12:42.428
UM, IT'S JUST A BUNCH
OF INK SPLATTERS, BUT, UH

12:42.511 --> 12:44.305
I GUESS WE HAVE SOME MODERN
ART LOVERS IN THE ROOM.

12:44.388 --> 12:45.764
UM, ARE YOU A CAVEMAN?

12:45.848 --> 12:49.685
HAVEN'T YOU EVER SEEN
A MAGICAL EYEBALL POSTER?

12:49.768 --> 12:52.897
THERE'S A HIDDEN PICTURE HIDING
IN THERE, AND IT'S RIGHT THERE.

12:54.774 --> 12:56.192
{\an3}SEE?

12:56.275 --> 12:58.652
COME ON, IT'S RIGHT THERE.

12:58.736 --> 13:00.237
[GROANING]

13:02.948 --> 13:04.366
JUST LOOK AT IT.

13:04.450 --> 13:06.035
YOU'RE NOT LOOKING AT IT RIGHT.

13:06.118 --> 13:07.661
COME ON, BESSIE.

13:07.745 --> 13:08.204
YOU CAN SEE IT TOO.

13:08.287 --> 13:11.165
CONCENTRATE.

13:11.248 --> 13:14.668
[GROANING]

13:14.752 --> 13:16.712
[PANTING]

13:16.795 --> 13:17.379
WHERE IS IT?

13:17.463 --> 13:19.715
DO YOU SEE IT YET?

13:19.798 --> 13:22.009
GIVE ME A MINUTE, PEN.

13:22.092 --> 13:25.346
{\an1}MAYBE YOU COULD SEE IT
IF YOU DON'T TRY SO HARD.

13:25.429 --> 13:26.514
THAT DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

13:26.597 --> 13:28.557
THE HARDER YOU TRY,
THE MORE YOU WIN.

13:28.641 --> 13:29.975
UGH, THINK ABOUT IT.

13:30.059 --> 13:31.101
LOOK, IT'S JUST A STUPID...

13:31.185 --> 13:31.977
OH, DON'T TELL ME.

13:32.061 --> 13:32.645
DON'T TELL ME.

13:32.728 --> 13:33.312
DON'T TELL ME.

13:33.395 --> 13:34.021
DON'T TELL ME.

13:34.104 --> 13:35.523
I WANT TO GET IT ON MY OWN.

13:35.606 --> 13:36.732
THAT'S ENOUGH GAWKING, GIRLS.

13:36.815 --> 13:38.901
WE'VE GOT A LOT
OF BUSINESS TO COVER.

13:38.984 --> 13:42.238
[GROANING]

13:42.321 --> 13:47.660
{\an5}AND THEN WE GOT ICE CREAM,
BUT I DIDN'T EAT MINE BECAUSE
I'M ALLERGIC TO COWS.

13:48.494 --> 13:50.412
THE END.

13:50.496 --> 13:52.957
GETTING WARMER.

13:56.544 --> 13:59.296
{\an5}GET THOSE PERMISSION SLIPS
TURNED IN TO ME
BY NEXT SATURDAY.

13:59.380 --> 14:00.381
TAKE ONE AND PASS IT BACK.

14:06.262 --> 14:07.304
ALMOST THERE.

14:07.388 --> 14:09.765
I CAN FEEL IT.

14:09.848 --> 14:10.474
FORGET IT.

14:10.558 --> 14:11.475
I DON'T EVEN WANT TO SEE.

14:11.559 --> 14:13.102
I DO WANT TO SEE IT SO BAD.

14:13.185 --> 14:13.811
WHERE IS IT?

14:13.894 --> 14:16.230
OH, GIVE IT TO ME.

14:16.313 --> 14:18.482
[SCREAMING]

14:18.566 --> 14:20.484
I KNOW YOU'RE IN THERE,
YOU STUPID PICTURE!

14:20.568 --> 14:22.570
YOU BETTER START RUNNING, 'CAUSE
I'M GONNA COME AND GET YOU.

14:30.953 --> 14:32.162
[SNORING]

14:32.246 --> 14:34.957
OUT.

14:35.040 --> 14:37.626
{\an5}YOU'VE ALREADY CUT DEEPLY
INTO MY SET-UP TIME
FOR THE PATTY FAYE SALE.

14:37.710 --> 14:40.462
{\an5}BUT MRS. GIBBONS,
THERE'S A HIDDEN PICTURE
IN THAT MAGICAL EYEBALL POSTER

14:40.546 --> 14:41.380
AND I HAVEN'T FOUND IT YET.

14:41.463 --> 14:45.092
OH, TAKE IT WITH YOU.

14:45.175 --> 14:49.597
{\an3}[BARKING]

14:49.680 --> 14:51.765
OH, DON'T TELL ME WHAT IT IS.

14:51.849 --> 14:52.474
I'LL GET IT.

14:52.558 --> 14:53.934
I DON'T WANT A HINT.

14:54.018 --> 14:57.104
{\an3}[BARKING]

14:57.187 --> 14:58.147
I <i> AM</i> RELAXED.

14:58.230 --> 14:59.857
EVERYBODY KEEPS TELLING ME
TO RELAX.

14:59.940 --> 15:01.317
I AM SO, SO RELAXED.

15:01.400 --> 15:01.984
JUST LOOK AT ME.

15:02.067 --> 15:03.694
LISTEN TO MY HEARTBEAT.

15:03.777 --> 15:04.153
[POUNDING]

15:04.236 --> 15:05.195
{\an3}[YELPING]

15:05.279 --> 15:06.989
AM I RIGHT?

15:07.072 --> 15:08.490
STEADY AS A ROCK, RIGHT?

15:08.574 --> 15:12.286
[HAPPY GROWLING]

15:12.369 --> 15:16.040
[WHIMPERING]

15:17.249 --> 15:21.795
{\an1}OM...

15:24.173 --> 15:25.924
{\an4}OM...

15:24.173 --> 15:25.924
[WHIMPERING]

15:27.468 --> 15:29.845
{\an4}OM...

15:27.468 --> 15:29.845
[WHIMPERING]

15:29.928 --> 15:33.307
{\an1}SUPPOSED TO CHECK
THE SMOKE DETECTOR.

15:33.390 --> 15:34.683
{\an4}OM...

15:33.390 --> 15:34.683
[WHIMPERING]

15:34.767 --> 15:38.354
SUPPOSED TO POLISH MY BADGES.

15:38.437 --> 15:40.814
{\an4}OM...

15:38.437 --> 15:40.814
[WHIMPERING]

15:40.898 --> 15:42.650
{\an1}DON'T FORGET TO TIGHTEN
THE LOOSE NUT.

15:42.733 --> 15:43.025
{\an1}NUT.

15:43.108 --> 15:44.193
{\an1}OH, NUTS.

15:44.276 --> 15:48.614
[BEEPING]

15:48.697 --> 15:49.865
[GROANING]

15:52.868 --> 15:56.538
{\an3}[GROWLING]

15:56.622 --> 15:57.456
I KNOW, I KNOW.

15:57.539 --> 15:58.415
{\an1}OH, WAIT.

15:58.499 --> 15:59.667
JUST ONE MORE THING, HAPPY.

15:59.750 --> 16:01.502
{\an1}PROMISE.

16:01.585 --> 16:03.796
{\an3}[GROWLING]

16:03.879 --> 16:06.340
{\an1}THESE ARE SO I CAN RELAX
TO THE SOUND OF THE OCEAN.

16:06.423 --> 16:10.511
{\an3}[GROWLING]

16:10.594 --> 16:14.890
{\an4}OM...

16:10.594 --> 16:14.890
[WHIMPERING]

16:14.973 --> 16:16.183
{\an1}THIS REALLY MAKES ME
HAVE TO PEE.

16:19.812 --> 16:21.355
{\an1}[BARKING]

16:30.531 --> 16:31.990
[SIGHING]

16:32.074 --> 16:34.535
SEE, THE PROBLEM IS,
THEY'RE DOING IT SO SLOW.

16:37.955 --> 16:38.539
DONE.

16:38.622 --> 16:40.040
I DID ALL THE MOVES.

16:40.124 --> 16:42.751
{\an3}[GROWLING]

16:42.835 --> 16:43.335
{\an1}[SCOFFING]

16:43.419 --> 16:44.712
HOW DO YOU THINK I FEEL?

16:44.795 --> 16:47.464
I'LL TELL YOU: NOT RELAXED.

16:47.548 --> 16:47.881
[HAPPY GROWLING]

16:47.965 --> 16:49.550
[SCOFFING]

16:49.633 --> 16:51.009
I <i> WILL</i> FIND SOMEONE ELSE
TO TEACH ME.

16:51.093 --> 16:54.012
{\an5}YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY ONE
WHO KNOWS HOW TO DO NOTHING
FOR A LONG TIME.

17:03.147 --> 17:06.358
[SLURPING]

17:06.442 --> 17:07.526
{\an1}[SIGHING]

17:07.608 --> 17:13.781
{\an3}[SIGHING]

17:13.866 --> 17:14.241
[KNUCKLES CRACK]

17:14.324 --> 17:17.786
[KNUCKLES CRACK]

17:17.869 --> 17:18.704
{\an3}[GASPING]

17:18.787 --> 17:20.622
DON'T YOU RECYCLE?

17:23.791 --> 17:26.252
IT'S EASY TO RELAX, BESSIE.

17:26.336 --> 17:27.253
WATCH.

17:27.337 --> 17:29.256
DUH...

17:29.339 --> 17:31.633
{\an1}[SNORING]

17:31.717 --> 17:34.344
{\an3}PENNY?

17:34.428 --> 17:35.971
[CAR HORN HONKING]

17:36.054 --> 17:41.894
{\an4}DUDE, I STILL HAVEN'T GOTTEN
MORE FAKE DOG POO,
SO DON'T EVEN ASK.

17:43.145 --> 17:43.562
[GRUMBLING]

17:43.645 --> 17:46.482
OH, HELLO, HAPPY.

17:46.565 --> 17:50.736
{\an5}PLEASE LET ME KNOW
WHEN YOU ARE DONE
ASSISTING YOUR OTHER CUSTOMER.

17:51.987 --> 17:54.323
WELL, I JUST HAVE
A SIMPLE QUESTION.

17:54.406 --> 17:56.158
DO YOU HAVE ANY SPECIAL GLASSES
THAT'LL LET ME SEE

17:56.241 --> 17:58.535
THE HIDDEN PICTURE
IN A MAGICAL EYEBALL POSTER?

17:58.619 --> 18:02.331
YOU'VE COME TO THE RIGHT MAN.

18:02.414 --> 18:03.916
[SPITTING]

18:03.999 --> 18:07.127
YOU DON'T NEED FANCY GLASSES.

18:07.211 --> 18:10.672
I CAN SEE ALL OF IT,
AND SO CAN YOU.

18:10.964 --> 18:12.883
{\an1}LOOK.

18:12.966 --> 18:16.512
{\an5}THAT'S AN OSTRICH
EATING SPAGHETTI MADE
OUT OF GUMMY WORMS.

18:16.595 --> 18:20.098
{\an5}THERE'S AN EPIC PIRATE BATTLE,
ONLY IT'S IN THE DESERT
AND NOT THE OCEAN.

18:23.227 --> 18:27.314
AND THAT'S ABRAHAM LINCOLN
BRUSHING A DRAGON'S MANE.

18:29.650 --> 18:32.569
{\an3}I KNOW, DRAGONS DON'T
USUALLY HAVE MANES.

18:32.653 --> 18:33.904
WEIRD, RIGHT?

18:33.987 --> 18:35.531
THAT'S WHAT I LOVE
ABOUT THESE THINGS.

18:35.614 --> 18:37.908
AND THIS ONE?

18:37.991 --> 18:40.202
THIS IS MY MOST BELOVED ONE.

18:40.285 --> 18:43.622
{\an6}I JUST LOOK AT IT
AND IT MAKES ME WANT TO WEEP,
'CAUSE IT'S SO BEAUTIFUL.

18:43.956 --> 18:46.625
{\an1}OH, NUTS!

18:46.708 --> 18:47.209
OK, HAPPY.

18:47.292 --> 18:49.002
I'M READY TO LEARN.

18:49.086 --> 18:50.254
[GROWLING]

18:50.337 --> 18:50.921
YOU'RE THE MASTER.

18:51.004 --> 18:51.797
YOU'RE THE MASTER.

18:51.880 --> 18:53.131
PLEASE, TEACH ME.

18:57.219 --> 18:59.930
Bessie: YOU HAVE A SECRET
SERENITY GARDEN?

19:00.013 --> 19:02.182
WOW.

19:02.266 --> 19:06.061
IT'S VERY RELAXING.

19:20.784 --> 19:23.495
{\an3}[GRUMBLING]

19:23.579 --> 19:25.372
{\an1}[BARKING]

19:40.679 --> 19:43.432
[GONG RINGING]

19:58.196 --> 20:00.657
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

20:23.513 --> 20:29.269
[CHORUS VOCALIZING...]

20:49.748 --> 20:51.458
LET'S DO THIS.

21:13.772 --> 21:15.691
WOW.

21:15.774 --> 21:17.693
HAPPY, HAPPY!

21:17.776 --> 21:20.654
I SAW IT!

21:20.737 --> 21:22.114
IT WAS INCREDIBLE.

21:22.197 --> 21:24.950
I UNDERSTAND EVERYTHING NOW.

21:25.033 --> 21:25.742
{\an1}OH, HAPPY.

21:25.826 --> 21:28.704
{\an1}ONE DAY, I HOPE
YOU EXPERIENCE IT.

21:28.787 --> 21:32.040
I SAW UNICORNS.

21:32.124 --> 21:33.375
{\an1}AND THEN THERE WERE
THESE BALLS OF LIGHTS

21:33.458 --> 21:35.085
{\an4}AND THEN THERE WERE
THESE FAIRIES, OR MAYBE
THEY WERE MERMAIDS.

21:35.168 --> 21:36.586
I DON'T KNOW, IT DOESN'T MATTER.

21:36.670 --> 21:39.298
ANYWAY, THEN EVERYTHING
GOT SUCKED INTO A BLACK HOLE.

21:41.425 --> 21:46.138
[MARKER SQUEAKING]

21:46.221 --> 21:49.933
[GRUMBLING]

21:50.017 --> 21:51.184
WHAT?

21:51.268 --> 21:53.562
[WHIMPERING]

21:57.482 --> 21:58.066
YEP.

21:58.150 --> 21:59.109
NOW, I'M RELAXED.

22:00.318 --> 22:06.283
[♪...]

22:40.192 --> 22:44.446
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]
